.SS clean
.PP
.I Remove stale/orphaned files from the ESP (dry\-run by default)
.PP
.B Category:
Maintenance
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-esp clean [\-\-apply] [\-\-keep\-backups] [\-\-esp PATH] [\-\-offline DISK] [\-\-json]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-apply
Actually remove files (default: preview only)
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-backups
Don\'t remove .bak files even if stale
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-esp clean
sudo lamboot\-esp clean \-\-apply
sudo lamboot\-esp clean \-\-keep\-backups \-\-apply
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Targets: macOS remnants (mach_kernel, System/), LamBoot backup files (*.lamboot\-backup), interrupted\-install temp files (*.lamboot\-tmp.*). NEVER removes bootloader binaries, BLS entries, or UKIs.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
Yes \- supports \fB\-\-offline\fR \fIDISK\fR
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
check, inventory
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/esp/clean
.UE
.RE
